LanguageData.JRWRhamphorhynchus.description:
-- > INGEN INTERNAL CASE FILE #08721-1839 [RHAMPHORHYNCHUS MUENSTERI] CODENAME: BEAK-SNOUT >382
A small pterosaur with a long tail. Their beak, bright red in colour, is lined with needle like teeth. They use these to eat small lizards, insects, fish, and the occasional finger.
